Even if the only use of lighting is to
»CL0:shade»CL1:  the  objects,  be careful where
you  place  light  sources  because it
»CL0:does»CL1:  matter.   Lightsources differ in
»CL0:type»CL1:   as  well;  »CL0:spotlights»CL1:,  »CL0:ambient
light»CL1:,  »CL0: sunlight»CL1:,   etc.    But  this
lighting can only really be controlled
with such »CL0:freedom»CL1: in the most »CL0:advanced»CL1:
3D  engines.  For those of you without
such  »CL0:code»CL1:  at  your  disposal, try to
work »CL0:around»CL1: the problems instead.


